<h1>Methodology</h1>

<p class="lede">This page explains how every claim on Food Transparency UK is recorded and what the words "confidence" and "evidence" mean when you see them next to a value.</p>

<aside class="caveat" role="note">
  <p class="caveat__heading">Provisional foundation stub</p>
  <p>This is an early foundation page. It describes the verification standard the archive is built to meet and defines the two trust grades. A later phase (Phase 7) finalises the full public methodology. Treat this version as provisional.</p>
</aside>

<h2>Two grades on every fact</h2>
<p>Each fact carries two separate grades, shown inline as plain text so they never depend on colour to be read. <strong>Confidence</strong> is how certain the curator is that the record is correct and current. <strong>Evidence</strong> is the strength of the underlying regulatory or scientific evidence. They are deliberately kept apart: a record can be confidently transcribed from a single source while the evidence behind the claim is still limited.</p>

